1. Create a new Next.js app using the command `npx create-next-app`.
2. Install the required dependencies for Python using `pip3 install`.
3. Create a new Python file in the root directory of your Next.js app.
4. Write a Python script that prints "Hello, World!" to the console.
5. In your Next.js app, create a new API route that calls the Python script using the `child_process` module.
6. In your Next.js app, create a new page that displays the output of the API route.
7. Build the Next.js app using `npm run build`.
8. Deploy the app to an Azure Web App using the Azure CLI or the Azure portal.
